Text.string: Typhon bought us our lives, but we're running out of last chances.
Even if Tyreen is stopped, Elpis is far too close to Pandora. The Great Vault will continue to open.
Let's worry about that when Tyreen is dead. One apocalypse at a time.
We're in orbit, VH. I got eyes on your fine ass from Sanctuary. Pandora's tearin' itself a new one, but I ain't lettin' you fight that mega-devilbitch alone.
Run towards the fire, Vault Hunter. Kick her ass.
Mmmnh... finally...
Don't expect mercy, superfan. I'm not that kind of god.
This is it, killer! Show her that gods can bleed!
Lilith, I may have a shortcut to where Tyreen went. This machine works across interstellar distances. There must be a way... yes, I can use the connection to Pandora to form a portal.
Where ya goin', superfan?
There! That's your opening. Give her hell!
I see everything now!
The eye on her back! That's your target!
She's down! Climb on her back!
Vault Hunter. Climb!
You've got her, Vault Hunter. Now climb!
She's down! Now's your chance!
Her back—you can climb her back!
You're nothing! I am endless!
Watch out!
Look out!
Run!
Retreat!
Head's up!
Yee-haw!
Vault Hunter! Ammo for ya!
Ca-kaw!
Hell yeah!

Killer, we'd be dead a thousand times over if it wasn't for you. I've been telling myself I still belonged on the front lines, but... a leader needs to know when to stand aside and let a soldier do their job. This is your fight.
Vaulty Vault! Shoot the bomb! Shoot the adorable bomb!
Gahagahaha! Ka-boom, biiiiiiitch!
RRAAGAHAAGHHHRGH!
You did it, killer. She's gone.
Well, would you look at that.
Go on. Vault's all yours.
Redemption at last... but one sacrifice remains.
Vault Hunter, did you hear that, too? Nevermind—come back out when you're ready. You've got some fans waiting for ya.
Vault Hunter, you did it! Tyreen's dead! For real, this time. She's... not gonna come back, is she?
Well, she died and turned to ash, so... I'm gonna give it a hard maybe.
You got your powers back. Feels good, right?
I spent so long without them, I'd almost gotten used to it. Not gonna lie, it does feel good.
All right, well... let's see what the Firehawk can do! C'mon, teleport us to Athenas. I know a great noodle shop.
The powers don't define you.
They sorta do.
Tyreen's powers didn't save her.
It's over.
Not... entirely.
The Great Vault is still opening. Elpis is tearing Pandora apart.
How do we stop it?
It's time. The Destroyer is escaping. You ready, killer?
Very simple. We can't. Not unless you know a way to remove the moon from the sky.
Run towards the fire.
Sanctuary's yours, Ava. Be ready.
What does Lilith think she's doing?
Closing the Great Vault.
That could kill her!
She knows.
She's the Firehawk.
She's gone.
Not entirely.
Just give the order, Commander. I'm ready.
I've never run from a fight, Commander.
I won't let you down, Commander. It's been an honor.
Oh yeah, Commander. I'm ITCHIN' for a fight.
This is the end. If Tyreen leeches the Destroyer, she'll be unstoppable.
It worked! Ah! It seems I can add “time and space” to the long list of things I have mastery over!
She's saving Pandora.
I assume you mean anything valuable to pilfer, but yes. Let us investigate.
Fragged a god. That's a first.
God-killer. Yeah... I like it.
Even GODS can be hunted!
Zane “God-Killer” Flynt! Hahahaha!
She's lighting the way.
Recruit, you did it! You followed my instructions exactly and saved Pandora! Oh, right. Ava wants to talk to you... she's in Lilith's room.
Attention, crew of Sanctuary. That motherf**kin' Vault Hunter just saved y'all asses, so show some respect! Ain't enough heroes in this galaxy.
Okay. This ends on Pandora, one way or the other. Head through the portal and find Tyreen. We'll see you on the other side.
I guess I was hopin' Lilith would be here waiting for us, but she's just... gone. Maya, she used to tell me stories about Lilith. When the two of them were fighting side-by-side. I miss them both.
We should go back up to Sanctuary. See if there's anything she left us.
We are in Lilith's quarters, Vault Hunter. Please bring me the Vault Key you retrieved from Tyreen.
Lilith had her own secrets back here. This chest is of Eridian design, but I have no idea where she might have gotten it. There's no external mechanism on it, but perhaps I can phaseshift it open.
Ah, so I can! Most peculiar. Lilith must have intended for me to find this, but that would mean... hmm. Nonetheless, there is another matter for us to discuss, Vault Hunter.

Using my enormous intellect, I have sussed out the purpose of the artifact you discovered inside the Vault. It is an advanced Guardian mind-core! I've created a neural adaptor that will link it up with the ship's fast-travel system. Please do so now.

The Guardians used that mind-core to improve their own combat AI by training in simulations of alternate, more chaotic universes! At least, I believe they were simulations. It's unclear, but don't be too concerned—any paradoxes or reality-leaks should either resolve themselves or we will all be obliterated before we can feel too much pain.
Sounds fun, doesn't it? I call it “Mayhem Mode”. I've integrated it into our onboard fast-travel map, so you can use it whenever you feel the call of mayhem! Enjoy!
We're counting on you, killer. The Destroyer is ripping the planet apart. You have to stop Tyreen. Pandora's always been a hellhole, but it's our hellhole, damn it.
